Class CardIOActivity

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentCallbacks, KeyEvent.Callback, LayoutInflater.Factory, View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, Window.Callback

    public final class CardIOActivity
extends Activity
    This is the entry point activity for a Card.IO client to use the Card.IO service. Please ensure that EXTRA_APP_TOKEN is set prior to creating this activity.
    Version:
    1.0

      • EXTRA_APP_TOKEN

        public static final String EXTRA_APP_TOKEN
        String extra. REQUIRED to use the Card.IO system. Get a valid app token at card.io. If this extra is not set, an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown when the activity is created.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXTRA_NO_CAMERA

        public static final String EXTRA_NO_CAMERA
        Boolean extra. Optional. Defaults to false. If set, the card will not be scanned with the camera. Does not apply to charge requests.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXTRA_REQUIRE_EXPIRY

        public static final String EXTRA_REQUIRE_EXPIRY
        Boolean extra. Optional. Defaults to true. Ignored for charge requests. If unset, expiry information will not be required.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXTRA_REQUIRE_CVV

        public static final String EXTRA_REQUIRE_CVV
        Boolean extra. Optional. Defaults to false. If set, the user will be prompted for the card CVV. For charge requests with manual entry, the user is always prompted.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXTRA_REQUIRE_ZIP

        @Deprecated
public static final String EXTRA_REQUIRE_ZIP
        Deprecated. Use EXTRA_REQUIRE_POSTAL_CODE instead.
        Boolean extra. Optional. Defaults to false. If set, the user will be prompted for the card billing postal code. For charge requests with manual entry, the user is always prompted.

        Will assume true if either EXTRA_REQUIRE_ZIP or EXTRA_REQUIRE_POSTAL_CODE is true.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXTRA_REQUIRE_POSTAL_CODE

        public static final String EXTRA_REQUIRE_POSTAL_CODE
        Boolean extra. Optional. Defaults to false. If set, the user will be prompted for the card billing postal code. For charge requests with manual entry, the user is always prompted.

        Will assume true if either EXTRA_REQUIRE_ZIP or EXTRA_REQUIRE_POSTAL_CODE is true.
        See Also:

      • EXTRA_SUPPRESS_MANUAL_ENTRY

        public static final String EXTRA_SUPPRESS_MANUAL_ENTRY
        Boolean extra. Optional. Defaults to false. Removes the keyboard button from the scan screen. If EXTRA_CHARGE_REQUEST is set, this value is ignored. If scanning is unavailable, the activity result will be RESULT_SCAN_NOT_AVAILABLE.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • EXTRA_LANGUAGE_OR_LOCALE

        public static final String EXTRA_LANGUAGE_OR_LOCALE
        String extra. Optional. The preferred language for all strings appearing in the user interface. If not set, or if set to null, defaults to the device's current language setting.

        Can be specified as a language code ("en", "fr", "zh-Hans", etc.) or as a locale ("en_AU", "fr_FR", "zh-Hant_HK", etc.).

        If the library does not contain localized strings for a specified locale, then will fall back to the language. E.g., "es_CO" -> "es".
        If the library does not contain localized strings for a specified language, then will fall back to American English.

        If you specify only a language code, and that code matches the device's currently preferred language, then the library will attempt to use the device's current region as well. E.g., specifying "en" on a device set to "English" and "United Kingdom" will result in "en_GB".

        These localizations are currently included:
        da, de, en, en_AU, en_GB, en_SV, es, es_MX, fr, he, it, ja, ko, nb, nl, pl, pt, pt_BR, ru, sv, tr, zh-Hans, zh-Hant_HK, zh-Hant_TW.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • canReadCardWithCamera

        public static boolean canReadCardWithCamera()
        Determine if the device supports card scanning. An ARM7 processor and Android SDK 8 or later are required. Additional checks for specific misbehaving devices may also be added.
        Returns:
        True if camera is supported. False otherwise.
